====================================

This project contains data from NASA's Earth Science Data and Information System.
These data have been modified by cropping them to a smaller spatial extent.
Unless the content is marked with a use restriction or license, data provided from a NASA-led mission are licensed as Creative Commons Zero (CC0).
Full data use guidance is available at https://www.earthdata.nasa.gov/engage/open-data-services-software-policies/data-use-guidance.


### Atmospheric Data Attribution

This project uses atmospheric data provided via the HAPI (Heliophysics Application Programming Interface) protocol.

The HAPI protocol and associated data services are developed and maintained by the NASA Heliophysics Data Environment Enhancements (HDEE) program.

Data accessed via HAPI are the property of the original data providers and are subject to their respective terms and conditions. Users should consult the data source documentation for specific citation requirements.

Example data citation:
"Data obtained via the HAPI protocol from [Instrument/Provider], accessed on [Date], courtesy of [Agency/Institute Name]."


### Sentinel-2 Imagery Attribution

This project includes Sentinel-2 satellite imagery provided by the Copernicus Programme and the European Space Agency (ESA).

These data are made available under the Copernicus Open Access Data Policy, which permits free and open reuse, including for commercial purposes, subject to proper attribution.

Copernicus data © European Union, ESA, and the respective data providers.

More information is available at: https://copernicus.eu/en/legal-notice
